{"_id":"fac220eb-d9c7-32a0-84b1-73be101ad75d","authorName":"Stephen Cleary","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"ad2250182ff26a84dda974e50cd94382","message":"It's possible that it may deadlock, depending on the implementation of FirstOrDefaultAsync (and the DbProvider implementation used by your EF connection).\r\n\r\nEven if it doesn't deadlock, though, it's just not a good idea. Why should your ASP.NET app go through the trouble of sending an asynchronous request to the database if it's just going to synchronously block on it? There's no benefit there.","postId":"2012_07_dont-block-on-async-code-abe2d9c7-c3e9-3ed8-827c-021686fa2310","replyTo":"42368e06-b678-3294-afc0-b4eaf064b425","date":"2017-10-16T21:44:46Z","timestamp":1508190286,"authorUserId":"disqus:stephen_cleary"}